<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="legal-adj">legal <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'liːɡl/    美 /'liːɡl/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>[只用于名词前] 法律上的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He offered guidance to poor black people on their legal problems.
他为穷苦黑人提供法律指导。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>合法的；法定的</strong></h4>
<p>反 illegal： </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a legal holiday
法定假日(BrEabankholiday)</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It's legal to turn right at a red light in most states.
大部分州的法律允许红灯时右转。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>legally /'liːɡəli/ adv   </p></div>